<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Brayden's Rants and Recipes (Posts about fudge)</title><link>https://bstreete.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://bstreete.github.io/categories/fudge.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents © 2025 &lt;a href="mailto:bstreete@users.noreply.github.com"&gt;Brayden Streeter&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2025 17:08:07 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Peanut Butter Fudge</title><link>https://bstreete.github.io/posts/recipes/peanut-butter-fudge/</link><dc:creator>All Recipes</dc:creator><description>&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_ingredients"&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;
&lt;colgroup&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;/colgroup&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;½ cup butter&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 cups package brown sugar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;½ cup milk&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 cup peanut butter&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon vanilla extract&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;3 cups confectioners' sugar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: modified the sugar and peanut butter amounts compared to the original recipe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_directions"&gt;Directions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;div class="olist arabic"&gt;
&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remove the pot from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Place confectioners' sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Pour in peanut butter mixture and beat with an electric mixer until smooth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pour peanut butter mixture into an 8x8-inch dish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chill until firm before slicing, about 1 hour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>dessert</category><category>fudge</category><guid>https://bstreete.github.io/posts/recipes/peanut-butter-fudge/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 Dec 2025 18:48:03 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Butterscotch Fudge</title><link>https://bstreete.github.io/posts/recipes/butterscotch-fudge/</link><dc:creator>Taste of Home</dc:creator><description>&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_ingredients"&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;
&lt;colgroup&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;/colgroup&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon plus 2 tablespoons butter, divided&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1-2/3 cups sugar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2/3 cup evaporated milk&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 teaspoon salt&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 cups miniature marshmallows&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 package (10 to 11 ounces) butterscotch chips&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 cup chopped walnuts, toasted&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon maple flavoring&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_directions"&gt;Directions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;div class="olist arabic"&gt;
&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Line an 8-in. square pan with foil and grease the foil with 1 teaspoon butter; set aside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In a large saucepan, combine the sugar, milk, salt and remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remove from heat; add the marshmallows, chips, nuts and maple flavoring.
Stir until marshmallows and chips are melted.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Let stand until set.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using foil, lift fudge out of pan.
Discard foil; cut fudge into 1-in squares.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>dessert</category><category>favorites</category><category>fudge</category><guid>https://bstreete.github.io/posts/recipes/butterscotch-fudge/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 13 Dec 2025 18:44:24 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>